reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good chassis and price!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a replacement chassis for my NAS server, as I gutted out the parts from my old case into this one. Works really well. The 4 preinstalled fans blow cool air, they are a little noisy but I don’t mind. Make sure you have right amount of molex connectors, 4 of them if you plan to utilize all fans. Works with my mini ITX motherboard and my 2, 3.5 inch Hard Drives. Fair warning the case alone is heavy, so be wise with what screws/supports you use to hold the computer. I’m very happy with my purchase. 10/10 would recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Overall great little chassis
reviews.reviewText: Great compact size for my project, which fit in my very compact middle Atlantic rack. Pretty good value, hit all the right notes for me. The airflow is awesome with this design and layout. I would prefer not to have the fans included if the price was lower. I did replace the fans anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Top quality server chassis!
reviews.reviewText: This is a very solid and well-built rack mountable server chassis in my opinion! Everything is set up and ready to go inside. It is just a matter of selecting and installing all the main components which can be chosen and tailored to the builder's preference. It is definitely a "bare bones" unit, but that is exactly what it is supposed to be. I do not have the components yet for my particular build, but the quality of this chassis is top notch. Therefore, this product earns the highest five star rating and recommendation from me!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good rack case, completely bare bones, except for the front panel and fans. Lotsa fans.
reviews.reviewText: So, I got this for a pfsense server. It's been awhile since I have built a PC, and it shows. The case is quite nice, however keep in mind there are ZERO front openings, it is all power button, USB, LEDs, and tons of vents for the fans, for which, there are quite a few. So you will need to make sure you have every other piece. It does come with a bunch of screws and such, so as long as you have your components, you should be good. Now, with the fans, you might want to assess the heat you're going to generate and plug in fans accordingly. Just my $0.02 as the number of fans can make quite a bit of noise. Server room, no biggie, leaving it in your theater room, kind of a biggie. Use this rack case accordingly and I think you will like it as the finish is nice and has a professional feel to it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for small servers that can use normal parts.
reviews.reviewText: This thing is great to build in with normal computer parts, which is really good for budget builds that use older consumer parts which have better power usage than top of the line server parts. The thing I like about this design is that while using consumer parts it's still rack mountable, which is great for people who don't want to use weird mounts or parts to put things in their rack that shouldn't be there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a pretty good 2U rack case. It's quite basic but that's not a bad thing. The fans are ok, not the quietest but easy enough to swap out if you want. There is pretty good air flow from what I can tell. I'm not running anything too power hungry but was able to fit an mATX and a few hard drives in without issue and the temps seem good. For the price it's a nice basic option.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars sturdy and plenty of room!
reviews.reviewText: this is now housing my new plex server, has plenty of room for an ITX board, with a low profile cpu cooler and gpu and a regular ATX sized power supple. compatible with a rack mount or even server drawer slides. great for the home lab! def recommend
